oor plans, and more along the way. Of particular note are recent structures on the Chicago River and south of the Loop that are proposing new definitions of comfort and extravagance. Featuring nearly 350 stunning images and a foreword by renowned Chicago author Sara Paretsky, this new edition of Chicago Apartments offers a wide-ranging look inside some of the Windy City’s most magnificent abodes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aApartment houseszIllinoiszChicago. 0aArchitecturezIllinoiszChicagoxHistory. 0aRoom layout (Dwellings)zIllinoiszChicagovDesigns and plans. 0aUpper classxDwellingszIllinoiszChicagovDesigns and plans. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh  aArchitecture book, Design, Interior, Decorating, Lake Michigan, Urban planning, Photography, Midwest, Luxury homes, Art, Coffee table book, Windy City, Art deco, Houses, Historic, Hardcover, Illustrated, Sky scraper, High-rise, City development, Floor plan, Building, Great fire, Chicago river, City of Broad Shoulders.1 aEdelstein, Teri J., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHarris, Neil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParetsky, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParetsky, Sara.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069309640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226610900423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226610900.jpg  a978-3-11-069309-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles